<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-14T10:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-14T10:16:00-05:00" n="77" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2129</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Roumania, Servia, and Bulgaria</hi>
                                (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-14T17:00:00+01:44">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1915, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 17, 7.42 p.
                                m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>130. It is believed an agreement has been signed between Bulgaria and
                            Turkey and that a German-Austrian army will shortly attack Servia in
                            which case it is believed that Roumania will join Servia. Roumania is
                            prepared for war.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vopicka</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>